---------------Install MariaDB---------------

We update first in order to get the latest packages with 
---> "sudo apt update"

Then we will install the mariaDB server
---> "sudo apt install mariadb-server"

Start the mariaDB service
---> "sudo systemctl start mariadb"

Enable Access mariaDB
---> "firewall-cmd --permanent --add-service=mysql
---> "firewall-cmd --reload"

then we will enable mysql security scripts
---> "sudo mysql_secure_installation"
